<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3926&amp;p=31150#p31150"><![CDATA[
You aren't handling odd clock jitter properly. It's really simple, if the APU is on an odd clock on the $4017 write, act as if the write was one clock later.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Fri Feb 22, 2008 4:48 pm</p><hr />
