- After 29830 cpu cycles, the test rom reads 4015h (lda $4015) to verify the frame irq flag. I'm with a problem: by default, the apu clocks <em>before</em> the cpu reads 4015h, causing the test rom to fail. I wonder if is this a cpu bug <strong>or</strong> a condition to set the irq flag later..?<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">      Step 4<br />29830 Set frame irq<br />-4015h reads 40 &#40;should be 00&#41;<br />29831 Clock linear &amp; length and set frame irq<br />29832 Set frame irq</div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Fri Feb 22, 2008 4:10 pm</p><hr />
